The National Working Committee of the All Progressives Congress has announced the lifting of the suspension of former Governor of Ogun State, Senator Ibikunle Amosun. The NWC also lifted the suspension of Governor Rotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State, and former Governor of Imo State, Senator Rochas Okorocha. The Committee, at its meeting, also lifted the suspension of the Director-General, Voice of Nigeria, Mr. Osita Okechukwu; and former Minister of Niger Delta Affairs, Usani Usani. The latest developments in the ruling party, according to insiders, may not be unconnected with the moves to resolve the lingering crisis in the party. Details later. 